Sentencas: Vanadium molybdenum oxide system (VxMo(1-x)Oy for x <= 0.13) is synthesized through reducing acidified vanadate and molybdate solution at 60 degrees C by passing hydrogen sulfide gas through the solution.
Titulo: Electrochemical behaviour and sulfur tolerance of VxMo(1-x)Oy as solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the mixed oxide is tested at various operation temperatures as an anode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC) under pure and 50 ppm H2S-containing hydrogen fuel.
Titulo: Electrochemical behaviour and sulfur tolerance of VxMo(1-x)Oy as solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The highest cell performance of 0.18 W cm(-2) peak power is reached at an operation temperature of 750 degrees C for dry H-2.
Titulo: Electrochemical behaviour and sulfur tolerance of VxMo(1-x)Oy as solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: It is found that the addition of 50 ppm H2S to the anode gas causes a 22% decrease in the cell peak power.
Titulo: Electrochemical behaviour and sulfur tolerance of VxMo(1-x)Oy as solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The loss in the cell performance is attributed to both gas conversion and diffusion.
Titulo: Electrochemical behaviour and sulfur tolerance of VxMo(1-x)Oy as solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Short-term regeneration tests indicate that 1 h-exposure to sulfur-free gas is insufficient for the reactivation of the cell performance.
Titulo: Electrochemical behaviour and sulfur tolerance of VxMo(1-x)Oy as solid oxide fuel cell anode
